        <p>&nbsp;</p>
        <p><big>         </big></p>
        <p><big>A real exponential signal is defined as</big></p>
        <p><big>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; <img title="Double click to edit" class="Wirisformula" alt="«math xmlns=¨http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML¨»«mi»x«/mi»«mo»(«/mo»«mi»t«/mi»«mo»)«/mo»«mo»=«/mo»«mi»A«/mi»«msup»«mi»e«/mi»«mrow»«mi»§#963;«/mi»«mi»t«/mi»«/mrow»«/msup»«/math»" src="/fckeditor/editor/plugins/fckeditor_wiris/integration/showimage.php?formula=2311078021cb3aad51fbe4d57e883902.png" align="middle"></big></p>
        <p><big>Where both <em>"A"</em> and<em> "</em></big><big><em>σ</em></big><big><em>"</em> are real. Depending on the value of "</big><big><em>σ</em></big><big>" the signals will be different. If <em>"</em></big><big><em>σ</em></big><big><em>"</em> is positive the signal <em>x(t)</em> is a growing exponential and if <em>"</em></big><big><em>σ</em></big><big><em>"</em> is negative then the signal <em>x(t)</em> is a decaying exponential. For </big><big><em>σ</em></big><big>=0, signal <em>x(t)</em> will be constant. Figure 10(a), 10(b) and 10(c) shows a dc signal, exponentially growing signal and exponentially decaying signal respectively.<br>
        </big></p>
        <table style="width: 890px; height: 241px;" align="center" border="0" cellpadding="1" cellspacing="1">
            <tbody>
                <tr>
                    <td><big><img src="/userfiles/7/image/sig2/dc_signal.jpg" alt="" align="absMiddle" height="172" width="250"></big></td>
                    <td><img alt="" src="/userfiles/7/image/sig6/sig8/grow_expon.jpg" align="absMiddle" height="186" width="250"></td>
                    <td><img alt="" src="/userfiles/7/image/sig6/sig8/decay_sig%281%29.jpg" align="absMiddle" height="189" width="250"></td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                    <td><big>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Fig.10(a) A dc signal</big></td>
                    <td><big>Fig.10(b) Exponentially growing signal</big></td>
                    <td><big>Fig.10(c) Exponentially decaying signal</big></td>
                </tr>
            </tbody>
        </table>
        <p>&nbsp;</p>
        <p>&nbsp;</p>
        <p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>
        <p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<big> &nbsp; </big><big><br>
        </big></p>
        <p><big>         </big></p>
        <p class="MsoNormal"><big>&nbsp;</big></p>
        <p><big>         </big></p>
        <p><big><span style="color: rgb(0, 0, 255);">&nbsp;</span><strong><span style="color: rgb(0, 0, 255);">Complex exponential Signal:</span></strong></big></p>
        <p class="MsoNormal">&nbsp;</p>
        <p><big>         </big></p>
        <p><big>The complex exponential signal is given by</big></p>
        <p class="MsoNormal"><big>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; <img src="/fckeditor/editor/plugins/fckeditor_wiris/integration/showimage.php?formula=811c9c03cba76d6b58d2231daf1e5b28.png" alt="«math xmlns=¨http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML¨»«mi»x«/mi»«mo»(«/mo»«mi»t«/mi»«mo»)«/mo»«mo»=«/mo»«mi»A«/mi»«msup»«mi»e«/mi»«mrow»«mi»s«/mi»«mi»t«/mi»«/mrow»«/msup»«/math»" class="Wirisformula" title="Double click to edit" align="middle">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</big></p>
        <p><big>         </big></p>
        <p><big>Where <em>"s"</em> is a complex variable and it is defined as&nbsp; </big></p>
        <p><big>         </big></p>
        <p class="MsoNormal"><big>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp; <img src="/fckeditor/editor/plugins/fckeditor_wiris/integration/showimage.php?formula=105b5f65ce95e8d174a7e45cf67bd2d9.png" alt="«math xmlns=¨http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML¨»«mi»s«/mi»«mo»=«/mo»«mi»§#963;«/mi»«mo»+«/mo»«mi»j«/mi»«mi»§#969;«/mi»«/math»" class="Wirisformula" title="Double click to edit" align="middle"></big></p>
        <p><big>         </big></p>
        <p><big>Therefore</big></p>
        <p><big>         </big></p>
        <p><big>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; <img title="Double click to edit" class="Wirisformula" alt="«math xmlns=¨http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML¨»«mi»x«/mi»«mo»(«/mo»«mi»t«/mi»«mo»)«/mo»«mo»=«/mo»«msup»«mi»e«/mi»«mrow»«mi»s«/mi»«mi»t«/mi»«/mrow»«/msup»«mo»=«/mo»«msup»«mi»e«/mi»«mrow»«mo»(«/mo»«mi»§#963;«/mi»«mo»+«/mo»«mi»j«/mi»«mi»§#969;«/mi»«mo»)«/mo»«mi»t«/mi»«/mrow»«/msup»«mo»=«/mo»«msup»«mi»e«/mi»«mrow»«mi»§#963;«/mi»«mi»t«/mi»«/mrow»«/msup»«msup»«mi»e«/mi»«mrow»«mi»j«/mi»«mi»§#969;«/mi»«mi»t«/mi»«/mrow»«/msup»«/math»" src="/fckeditor/editor/plugins/fckeditor_wiris/integration/showimage.php?formula=1bfc38da7155dc2fe1f34e74a5bed646.png" align="middle"></big><big>&nbsp;&nbsp; ........................(1)</big></p>
        <p><big>         </big></p>
        <p><big>Using Eulers identity </big></p>
        <p><big>         </big></p>
        <p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp; <span style="font-size: 16pt; line-height: 115%;"><img title="Double click to edit" class="Wirisformula" alt="«math xmlns=¨http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML¨»«msup»«mi»e«/mi»«mrow»«mi»j«/mi»«mi»§#969;«/mi»«mi»t«/mi»«/mrow»«/msup»«mo»=«/mo»«msup»«mi»e«/mi»«mrow»«mi»j«/mi»«mi»§#952;«/mi»«/mrow»«/msup»«mo»=«/mo»«mi mathvariant=¨normal¨»cos«/mi»«mi»§#952;«/mi»«mo»+«/mo»«mi»j«/mi»«mi mathvariant=¨normal¨»sin«/mi»«mi»§#952;«/mi»«/math»" src="/fckeditor/editor/plugins/fckeditor_wiris/integration/showimage.php?formula=9def5d435a25b8648184d895becd6c02.png" align="middle">&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;</span><big>...............................(2)</big><span style="font-size: 16pt; line-height: 115%;"> </span></p>
        <p><big>Substituting eq<sup>n</sup>.(2) in eq<sup>n</sup>.(1) we have</big></p>
        <p>&nbsp;</p>
        <p><big>         </big></p>
        <p><big>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp; <img title="Double click to edit" class="Wirisformula" alt="«math xmlns=¨http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML¨»«mi»x«/mi»«mo»(«/mo»«mi»t«/mi»«mo»)«/mo»«mo»=«/mo»«msup»«mi»e«/mi»«mrow»«mi»§#963;«/mi»«mi»t«/mi»«/mrow»«/msup»«mo»[«/mo»«mi mathvariant=¨normal¨»cos«/mi»«mi»§#952;«/mi»«mo»+«/mo»«mi»j«/mi»«mi mathvariant=¨normal¨»sin«/mi»«mi»§#952;«/mi»«mo»]«/mo»«/math»" src="/fckeditor/editor/plugins/fckeditor_wiris/integration/showimage.php?formula=8293ff8956874e471e21a2cb29784a40.png" align="middle"></big></p>
        <p><big>&nbsp;A complex exponential signal can not be plot in a two dimentional (2D) graph, it should be plot in a three </big><big>dimentional graph. Figure given below shows the three dimentional view of a complex exponential signal.<br>
        </big></p>
        <p>&nbsp;</p>
        <p><big>Real sines and real cosines can be expressed by the combinations of complex sinusoids through the trigonometric identities </big></p>
        <p><big>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; <img title="Double click to edit" class="Wirisformula" alt="«math xmlns=¨http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML¨»«mi mathvariant=¨normal¨»cos«/mi»«mo»(«/mo»«mi»§#952;«/mi»«mo»)«/mo»«mo»=«/mo»«mfrac»«mrow»«msup»«mi»e«/mi»«mrow»«mi»j«/mi»«mi»§#952;«/mi»«/mrow»«/msup»«mo»+«/mo»«msup»«mi»e«/mi»«mrow»«mo»-«/mo»«mi»j«/mi»«mi»§#952;«/mi»«/mrow»«/msup»«/mrow»«mn»2«/mn»«/mfrac»«/math»" src="/fckeditor/editor/plugins/fckeditor_wiris/integration/showimage.php?formula=c08b3d43852146c2536596acb03ab59b.png" align="middle"></big>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; <big>and</big>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; <img title="Double click to edit" class="Wirisformula" alt="«math xmlns=¨http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML¨»«mi mathvariant=¨normal¨»sin«/mi»«mo»(«/mo»«mi»§#952;«/mi»«mo»)«/mo»«mo»=«/mo»«mfrac»«mrow»«msup»«mi»e«/mi»«mrow»«mi»j«/mi»«mi»§#952;«/mi»«/mrow»«/msup»«mo»-«/mo»«msup»«mi»e«/mi»«mrow»«mo»-«/mo»«mi»j«/mi»«mi»§#952;«/mi»«/mrow»«/msup»«/mrow»«mrow»«mi»j«/mi»«mn»2«/mn»«/mrow»«/mfrac»«/math»" src="/fckeditor/editor/plugins/fckeditor_wiris/integration/showimage.php?formula=0349fc578df9cc41251d900d6ae6b53e.png" align="middle">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>
        <p><big>Complex exponential signal<img title="Double click to edit" class="Wirisformula" alt="«math xmlns=¨http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML¨»«mo»(«/mo»«msup»«mi»e«/mi»«mrow»«mi»j«/mi»«mi»§#952;«/mi»«/mrow»«/msup»«mo»)«/mo»«/math»" src="/fckeditor/editor/plugins/fckeditor_wiris/integration/showimage.php?formula=54ea8fbf583d1a63dd08925a3bae1f38.png" align="middle">, out of phase complex exponential signal<img title="Double click to edit" class="Wirisformula" alt="«math xmlns=¨http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML¨»«mo»(«/mo»«msup»«mi»e«/mi»«mrow»«mo»-«/mo»«mi»j«/mi»«mi»§#952;«/mi»«/mrow»«/msup»«mo»)«/mo»«/math»" src="/fckeditor/editor/plugins/fckeditor_wiris/integration/showimage.php?formula=c23fd3ddfb7d0e37561066cc9ded938a.png" align="middle">and the addition and substraction of complex exponentials to </big><big>form the real cosine and real sine</big> <big>are </big><big>shown in Figure 11(a), 11(b), 11(c) and 11(d) respectively.</big></p>
        <p><big>&nbsp;</big></p>
        <p><big>         </big></p>
        <p><big><span style="font-size: 16pt; line-height: 115%;">&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; </span></big><big><small><big><span style="font-size: 12pt; line-height: 115%;"><img src="/userfiles/7/image/sig6/sig8/cp1.jpg" alt="" align="absMiddle" height="263" width="300">&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp; <img src="/userfiles/7/image/sig6/sig8/cp2.jpg" alt="" align="absMiddle" height="264" width="300"> <br>
        </span></big></small></big></p>
        <p><big>         </big></p>
        <p><big>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp; Fig.11(a) Complex exponential signal <img title="Double click to edit" class="Wirisformula" alt="«math xmlns=¨http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML¨»«msup»«mi»e«/mi»«mrow»«mi»j«/mi»«mi»§#952;«/mi»«/mrow»«/msup»«/math»" src="/fckeditor/editor/plugins/fckeditor_wiris/integration/showimage.php?formula=95dbfd1878296da7a020240fc46d3c42.png" align="middle">&nbsp;&nbsp; Fig.11(b) Out of phase complex exponential signal<img title="Double click to edit" class="Wirisformula" alt="«math xmlns=¨http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML¨»«msup»«mi»e«/mi»«mrow»«mo»-«/mo»«mi»j«/mi»«mi»§#952;«/mi»«/mrow»«/msup»«/math»" src="/fckeditor/editor/plugins/fckeditor_wiris/integration/showimage.php?formula=9fc2f71b9a31a951043983d207964f9b.png" align="middle"><br>
        </big></p>
        <p><big><big><small><span style="font-size: 12pt; line-height: 115%;">&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; <img src="/userfiles/7/image/sig6/sig8/cp3.jpg" alt="" align="absMiddle" height="267" width="300"> &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></small></big></big><big><big><img src="/userfiles/7/image/sig6/sig8/cp4.jpg" alt="" align="absMiddle" height="267" width="300"></big></big></p>
        <p>&nbsp;</p>
        <p><big>Fig.11(c)Real cosine after addition of complex sinusoids </big><big>Fig.11(d) Real sine after substraction of complex sinusoids<br>
        </big></p>
        <p><big><br>
        </big></p>
        <p>&nbsp;</p>
        <p><big>         </big><big><big>         </big></big><big>         </big><big><big><span style="font-size: 12pt; line-height: 115%;">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;</span><span style="font-size: 12pt; line-height: 115%;">&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp; </span><blink><a href="http://iitg.vlab.co.in/?sub=59&amp;brch=166&amp;sim=618&amp;cnt=1#link10"><span style="color: rgb(0, 0, 255);"><span style="font-size: 12pt; line-height: 115%;">Top<img alt="" src="http://iitg.vlab.co.in/fckeditor/editor/images/smiley/msn/thumbs_up.gif" align="absMiddle"></span></span></a></blink><span style="font-size: 12pt; line-height: 115%;"><br>
        </span><a href="http://iitg.vlab.co.in/?sub=59&amp;brch=166&amp;sim=618&amp;cnt=1#link1"><span style="color: rgb(51, 102, 255);"><span style="font-size: medium;"><br>
        </span></span></a></big></big></p>
